that the=20
anchor location for this object shall not be modified at runtime when an =

application edits the contents of this document. [Guidance: An =
application might=20
have automatic behaviors which reposition the anchor for a DrawingML =
object=20
based on user interaction - for example, moving it from one page to =
another as=20
needed. This element shall tell applications not to perform any such =
behaviors.=20
end guidance]</I><BR><BR>As I understand it, this means that, once you =
set the=20
"locked" attribute for an inline graphic, the application <I>shall =
not</I>=20
provide anyway to unset it or even to delete the graphic, which doesn't =
make=20
much sense. This clause should be written more narrowly to make it clear =
that=20
the application can changed the locked setting as a result of an =
explicit user=20
indication, at least.<BR><BR>In the same anchor element, there is also a =

"relativeHeight" attribute: <BR><BR><I>Specifies the relative Z-ordering =
of all=20
DrawingML objects in this document. Each floating DrawingML object shall =
