Z-ordering value, which determines which object is displayed when any =
two=20
objects intersect. Higher values shall indicate higher Z-order; lower =
values=20
shall indicate lower Z-order.</I><BR><BR>Problem: It doesn't specify =
what should=20
be done if two objects have the same Z-ordering value, nor does it state =
that=20
the Z-ordering values must be distinct.<BR><BR>I searched the proposed =
BRM=20
resolutions, and neither of these seems to be addressed.<BR>
